MAKETRI
Algorithmic Complexity: O(n)

1. Input values of n,l,r
2. For n inputs
	store values of n elements in a data structure like array or vector
3. Find the two largest elements in the array/vector
4. Find the two smallest elements in the array/vector
5. Assign max = sum of the two largest elements - 1 (To make range inclusive)
6. Assign min = absolute difference of the smallest two elements + 1
7. Set count to 0
8. if r<min or l>max:
	count=0
   else if l<=min and r>=min and r<=max:
	count = r-min+1
   else if l<=min and r>=max:
	count = max-min+1
   else if l>min and r<=max:
	count = r-l+1
   else if l>min and r>=max:
	count = max-l+1;
9. Print count
	
